    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://yatindandi.github.io/home/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Apr 2016 00:00:00 +0530</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://yatindandi.github.io/home/about/</guid>
      <description>&amp;ldquo;The only real limitations on making ‘machines which think’ are our own limitations in not knowing exactly what ‘thinking’ consists of.&amp;rdquo;
I am a sophomore at the Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur majoring in Computer Science and Engineering. My goal is to understand the computational building blocks of intelligence and consciousness through probabilistic modelling techniques applied to machine learning systems as well as the human mind. To this end, I have been working with the state of the art approaches to building intelligent systems such as Deep Learning and Reinforcement Learning.</description>
    </item>
    
